I"©<h2 id="brake-pedal-adjustment">Brake Pedal Adjustment</h2>

<p>After fitting a new master cylinder or servo, you may end up with free play at the top of the brake pedal. No amount of bleeding will remove this. The correct procedure is to take up the slack by adjusting the brake switch on the back of the pedal box.</p>

